      "content": "Those are okay for a starting point, but they're a bit \"policy-lite.\" For a high-level tournament, my students need to go deeper into the principled side of the debate. They need to be able to articulate the arguments regarding national sovereignty, the rule of law, and even the idea of social cohesion or the \"social contract.\" Could you expand on those more foundational, philosophical justifications for strict enforcement? They need to be able to present these as strong, legitimate standpoints.",
